Its high  antitumor activity against  several solid tumors (2,3) incited  phar-  macological  and  preclinical  investiga-  tions  (4). In  this paper we describe the separation and  structure elucidation  of  two major con-  stituents of retamycin. ABSTFLKT.-TWO major constituents, retarnycins E l  11) and E2 [2), were isolated from  the anthracyclinic complex retamycin. Both compounds  are  derivatives of y-rhodomycinone  glycosidically linked to rhodosamine. In addition, 1 contains two molecules of rhodinose and 2  one ofeach rhodinose and deoxyfucose. Composition, sequence, and stereochemical details were  determined by  high field  'H nmr spectroscopy and fabms. 1 and 2 were found to be identical  with rhodilunancins A and B (= cosmomycins A and B). Two kinds of  sequence  ions,  both  containing  the  y-  rhodomycinone  moiety,  were  observed  in  the spectrum (Figure  1).  In one case  fragmentation  occurs  at  the glycosidic  linkage  level,  generating  carbenium  ions described by  structures I and I' at  mlz 624, 5 10, and 353 (the first and the  last  ones  are  particularly  abundant). These  ions  indicate the sequence y-rhodomycinone-  rhodosamine-rhodinohodinose  for  1.  The spectrum of  the tetraacetyl deriva-  tive  confirmed  these  findings by  peaks  occurring at mlz [MH]+ 924,768,750,  and 654. GENERAL EXPERIMENTAL  PROCEDURE5.-  Melting  points are uncorrected.  'H  nmr spectra  were recorded on a Bruker W M  400 spectrometer  using CDCI,  as solvent and T M S  as an internal  standard. Fabms were run in bis(2-hydroxyethyl)  sulfide as the  matrix  on a Kratos MS 80 instru-  ment,  equipped  with  post-acceleration detector  and high-field magnet, using a Xenon beam of 6  keV energy and a current of ca.  30 FA.  Acetyla-  tion was carried out on analytical samples for 36  h,  using  pyridine-Ac,O  (1: 1).  Volatiles  were  evaporated  by  an  N2 current  before  taking  the  mass  spectra of  the  crude  acetylation mixture.  Acidic  hydrolysis  and  tlc  analysis of  the  sugars  were carried out according to Oki and co-workers  (68).
